Landscape-level fire-diversity analysis

Fire data polygons (or any spatial assets) spatially joined to biodiversity data from GBIF (or any similarly geocoded diversity data).

Data

First crack - birds.

#libraries
library(tidyverse)
library(skimr)

#count data
data <- read_csv("data/counts.csv") %>% 
  rename(ID = JOIN_FID, fire = FIRE_YEARn, site = INCIDENT, size = GISAcres, total_count = TotalBird)

#skim for QA/AC
#skim(data)

#tidy  
sites <- data %>% 
  group_by(ID) %>% 
  summarise(fire = mean(fire), size = as.integer(max(size)))
  
tidy <- data %>% 
  group_by(ID, year) %>% 
  summarise(total_count = total_count) 

tidy <- left_join(sites, tidy, by = "ID")
